  "texts": [
    "By removing these outliers, the execution times more accurately represent the program's behavior under normal conditions, free from external interference.",
    "The choice of 10 runs was determined based on empirical testing.",
    "After running the program for both 10 and 20 iterations, it was observed that the execution times between 10 and 20 runs did not differ significantly.",
    "The additional runs (beyond 10) did not improve the stability or reliability of the measurements.",
    "Therefore, 10 runs provided a good balance between accuracy and efficiency, reducing unnecessary computation while still capturing enough data to mitigate variability in execution times.Finally, to validate the reliability of the measurement, for each of the case studies, 1000 unique random inputs are used."
